<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="1342" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1342">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/106.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to Consul <persName type="to">Letcher</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-08">
                                        <hi rend="italic">January 8, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Investigate and report as to responsibility for killing of two
                                Spanish subjects whose bodies were recently found in or near
                                Chihuahua, and also as to action, if any, taken by authorities to
                                ascertain responsibility and punish guilty persons.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>